iel \\\"Kwikstep\\\" Dionisio\", \"from\": 376, \"to\": 403}, {\"ngram\": \"Ana \\\"Rokafella\\\" Garcia\", \"from\": 408, \"to\": 430}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The particularly devastating angle to the whole mess - \\\"frustrating, insulting, offensive\\\" is how Rokafella puts it; \\\"burning the scene\\\" is how Kwikstep sees it - was that it completely overshadowed the other performers, some of whom did win medals and \\\"made an incredible impression on that dance floor\\\".\", \"from\": 435, \"to\": 740, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The particularly devastating angle\", \"from\": 435, \"to\": 469}, {\"ngram\": \"the whole mess\", \"from\": 473, \"to\": 487}, {\"ngram\": \"Rokafella\", \"from\": 533, \"to\": 542}, {\"ngram\": \"the scene\", \"from\": 561, \"to\": 570}, {\"ngram\": \"Kwikstep\", \"from\": 579, \"to\": 587}, {\"ngram\": \"the other performers\", \"from\": 634, \"to\": 654}, {\"ngram\": \"medals\", \"from\": 677, \"to\": 683}, {\"ngram\": \"an incredible impression\", \"from\": 694, \"to\": 718}, {\"ngram\": \"that dance floor\", \"from\": 722, \"to\": 738}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's a huge shame, they say, because dancers such as Ami Yuasa (B-Girl Ami) from Japan who won the gold medal in the women's (\\\"b-girls\\\") breaking competition and Philip Kim (B-Boy Phil Wizard) from Canada who won a gold medal for the men's (\\\"b-boys\\\") competition, should have come away from the games covered in glory.\", \"from\": 750, \"to\": 1068, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 831, \"end\": 836, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"score\": 0.999756466302257, \"rank\": 0.00024356526938101834, \"text\": \"Japan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\"}, {\"begin\": 948, \"end\": 954, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.232552805368016e-14, \"text\": \"Canada\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a huge shame\", \"from\": 755, \"to\": 767}, {\"ngram\": \"dancers\", \"from\": 787, \"to\": 794}, {\"ngram\": \"B-Girl Ami\", \"from\": 814, \"to\": 824}, {\"ngram\": \"the gold medal\", \"from\": 845, \"to\": 859}, {\"ngram\": \"the women's (\\\"b\", \"from\": 863, \"to\": 878}, {\"ngram\": \"girls\", \"from\": 879, \"to\": 884}, {\"ngram\": \"B-Boy Phil Wizard\", \"from\": 924, \"to\": 941}, {\"ngram\": \"a gold medal\", \"from\": 963, \"to\": 975}, {\"ngram\": \"the men's (\\\"b\", \"from\": 980, \"to\": 993}, {\"ngram\": \"boys\", \"from\": 994, \"to\": 998}, {\"ngram\": \"the games\", \"from\": 1041, \"to\": 1050}, {\"ngram\": \"glory\", \"from\": 1062, \"to\": 1067}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Many in the breaking community had hoped the art form would grow in popularity and attract a wider audience after the International Olympic Committee announced that it would become an official sport at the Paris 2024 games.\", \"from\": 1070, \"to\": 1293, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1188, \"end\": 1219, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 1276, \"end\": 1286, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.500098555265106e-26, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the breaking community\", \"from\": 1078, \"to\": 1100}, {\"ngram\": \"the art form\", \"from\": 1111, \"to\": 1123}, {\"ngram\": \"popularity\", \"from\": 1138