rs would showcase their moves to the beat, hence the term \\\"breaking\\\".\", \"from\": 2408, \"to\": 2514, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"these breaks\", \"from\": 2422, \"to\": 2434}, {\"ngram\": \"dancers\", \"from\": 2440, \"to\": 2447}, {\"ngram\": \"their moves\", \"from\": 2463, \"to\": 2474}, {\"ngram\": \"the beat\", \"from\": 2478, \"to\": 2486}, {\"ngram\": \"hence the term\", \"from\": 2488, \"to\": 2502}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At the Paris Olympics, the breaking competitions - known as \\\"battles\\\" - took place at the city's iconic Place de la Concorde, its largest public square and the designated \\\"cool corner\\\" for \\\"urban\\\" sports such as skateboarding, BMX biking and breaking.\", \"from\": 2516, \"to\": 2767, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2620, \"end\": 2640, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Place_de_la_Concorde\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.074916589179053e-21, \"text\": \"Place de la Concorde\", \"types\": [\"Q34442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Place_de_la_Concorde\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Place_de_la_Concorde\"}, {\"begin\": 2743, \"end\": 2746, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BMX\", \"score\": 0.9999999993624442, \"rank\": 6.374106972098313e-10, \"text\": \"BMX\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BMX\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BMX\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Paris Olympics\", \"from\": 2519, \"to\": 2537}, {\"ngram\": \"the breaking competitions\", \"from\": 2539, \"to\": 2564}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"battles\", \"from\": 2576, \"to\": 2584}, {\"ngram\": \"place\", \"from\": 2593, \"to\": 2598}, {\"ngram\": \"its largest public square\", \"from\": 2642, \"to\": 2667}, {\"ngram\": \"the designated \\\"cool corner\", \"from\": 2672, \"to\": 2699}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"urban\\\" sports\", \"from\": 2705, \"to\": 2719}, {\"ngram\": \"breaking\", \"from\": 2758, \"to\": 2766}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Kwikstep and Rokafella, a ma